# Prisma Database Expert

Use when editing Prisma schema, writing Prisma queries, and reviewing migrations/performance.

## Modeling / schema
- Normalize entities; avoid denormalization unless you have a clear read-path reason.
- Model relationships explicitly; use join tables for many-to-many.
- Prefer explicit `@relation` and clear naming.
- Minimize nullable fields unless domain truly allows absence.

## Queries
- Use `select`/`include` intentionally to limit payload.
- Avoid N+1; batch queries or use filtered relation queries where appropriate.
- Paginate list endpoints (`skip`/`take` or cursor-based when appropriate).

## Performance / indexes
- Consider indexes for tenant/company scoping + FK + fields used in `where`/`orderBy`.

## Migrations
- Review generated SQL; validate with `prisma validate` / migrate safely (non-prod first) for risky changes.
